To fix the code quality issue of having a `console.log` statement in production code, you can remove or comment out the `console.log` statement in the `route.ts` file.

Here is an example of how you can remove the `console.log` statement:

Before:
```typescript
console.log("Logging data for debugging purposes:", data);
```

After:
```typescript
// console.log("Logging data for debugging purposes:", data);
```

By removing or commenting out the `console.log` statement, you can ensure that no debug information is being output to the console in production code, which can improve code quality and security.